verses.roman:
uṭhi' mahāprabhu vismita, iti uti cāya
ye dekhite cāya, tāhā dekhite nā pāya

synonyms: uṭhi'-standing up; mahāprabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; vismita—astonished; iti uti—here and there; cāya—looks; ye—what; dekhite cāya—He wanted to see; tāhā—that; dekhite nā pāya—He could not see.
translation: Astonished, Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu stood up and began looking here and there, trying to see something. But He could not catch sight of it.
